<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,225,396]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">
Material examined: Alto Rio Senguer: 
<taxonomicName box="[586,794,261,287]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Mulinum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosun">
<emphasis box="[586,794,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Mulinum spinosun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(6). The species was only recorded under shrub steppe. Records in 
<collectingCountry box="[277,393,297,323]" name="Argentina" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Argentina</collectingCountry>
: first record (
<collectingRegion box="[541,736,297,324]" country="Argentina" name="Chubut" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Chubut province</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,225,396]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">
Comments: the species was originally described in 
<collectingCountry box="[735,887,333,360]" name="New Zealand" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hammer" authorityYear="1968" box="[927,1147,334,359]" class="Arachnida" family="Oppiidae" genus="Lanceoppia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moritzi">
<emphasis box="[927,1147,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Lanceoppia moritzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Hammer (1968), who found four specimens under wet moss in a 
<taxonomicName box="[632,761,369,395]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[632,761,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Nothofagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest. It is the first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[1105,1220,369,395]" name="Argentina" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
